e"><CodeD index="no" lang="en">Living/Lifestyle</CodeD><CodeI org="expansion" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001000-20180323-161933"/><CodeA name="root" value="ns:gfas"/></CodeI><CodeI org="validation" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001000-20180323-161933"/><CodeA name="status" value="active"/></CodeI><CodeI org="hierarchy" action="add"><CodeA name="db" value="pedv---00001000-20180323-161933"/><CodeA name="nodelevel" value="1"/></CodeI></Code></CSet></CodeSets><DescTPC fid="de"><DescField fid="ipd">WSJ WSJ.com WSJ.com Site Search WSJAsia WSJEurope WSJ Japanese Online WSJ-PRO-WSJ.com WSJSunday HALF ZIP SWEATSHIRT HOODIE MEN'S CASUAL WEAR MEN'S FASHION MEN'S HOODIES MEN'S LEISUREWEAR MEN'S SWEATSHIRT REIGNING CHAMP SHOULD I WEAR A HOODIE SWEATER TRES BIEN SB111830843868116142765045841117237079838301 SYND CODES_REVIEWED Fashion </DescField><DescField fid="ipcns">OLEM OLSF </DescField></DescTPC></MetadataPT><ArchiveDoc xml:space="preserve"><Article markup="pp0" lang="en" index="field"><HandL fid="hlp"><Title fid="hl"><SectionName fid="se" index="field">Life</SectionName><ColumnName fid="clm" index="field"></ColumnName><Headline fid="hd"><Para lang="en">Move Over Hoodies: The Half-Zip Has Arrived; Increasingly popular, the half-zip sweatshirt offers men the best of both worlds—blending the casual slouch of a hoodie and dressier look of a merino work sweater</Para></Headline></Title><LeadPara fid="lp"><Para>THE HALF-ZIP sweatshirt is having an identity crisis. It's not as casual as your standard hoodie, yet it can't quite keep a straight face like a middle-management merino sweater. The good news: By straddling that line between relaxed and refined, it's doing men a favor.</Para><Para>"I can see a guy wearing khakis with this and I can see a guy wearing sweatpants with this," said Jose Villanueva, co-owner of Chicago menswear shop Notre, of the new half-zip sweatshirt from Sweden's Très Bien that he recently stocked. "It's pretty damn versatile."</Para></LeadPara></HandL><TailParas fid="td"><Para>A descendant of your dad's trusty game-day pullover, the half-zip has benefited from a designer makeover. In trimmer silhouettes, premium cotton fabrics and less banal shades and patterns, the newer iterations function as an everyday spring layer that's just polished enough.</Para><Para>Tung Vo, creative director at the Vancouver, British Columbia-based label Reigning Champ, called his recently introduced half-zip sweatshirt a "hybrid of sorts," equipping guys to deploy a little "casual flair" while still looking sufficiently dressed up.</Para><Para>You can throw a half-zip over jeans and schlumpy loafers for a wholly mellow Saturday brunch look, but come Monday, the trim shape of the chameleonic piece pairs so neatly atop a button-up and trousers that your boss won't look askance.</Para><Para>Simon Hogeman, co-founder of Très Bien, would be surprised to see sales of half-zips outpacing those of hoodies soon, but for him the hybrids are a welcome alternative. He said he wears a hoodie about five days a week, but likes to mix it up now that he's reached the ripe age of 34 and "would probably qualify as a grown up."</Para><Para>Familiar yet not. Pullover, $140, <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://reigningchamp.com/">reigningchamp.com</ELink></Para><Para>More polished in black. Pullover, $360, <ELink type="webpage" ref="https://www.acnestudios.com/us/en/home">acnestudios.com</ELink></Para><Para>Pink stripes for the win. Pullover, $185, <ELink type="webpage" ref="http://tres-bien.com/">tres-bien.com</ELink></Para></TailParas><Byline fid="by" index="field">By Chris Kornelis </Byline><Credit fid="cr" index="field"></Credit><Contact fid="ct" index="field"></Contact><Notes fid="rf" index="field"></Notes><Art fid="art" index="field"></Art><Copyright fid="cy" index="field">Copyright 2018 Dow Jones &amp; Company, Inc. All Rights Reserved. </Copyright></Article></ArchiveDoc><AdocTOC adoctype="article"><Item size="0" ref="di